==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tink
<hw>Tink</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tinken</ets>; of imitative origin. Cf. <er>Ting</er> a tinkling,
<er>Tinker</er>.]</ety> <def>To make a sharp, shrill noise; to
tinkle.</def> <rj><au>Wyclif (1 Cor. xiii. 1).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tink
<hw>Tink</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sharp, quick sound; a
tinkle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tinker</ent>⟦br⟧
